00:25:42,109 --> 00:25:45,010
...until they've stolen enough
to go into exile somewhere else.

245
00:25:45,178 --> 00:25:47,806
And the rebels, they're not sure
they want to take over.

246
00:25:47,981 --> 00:25:50,313
Otherwise,
they'd have to govern this mess.

247
00:25:50,484 --> 00:25:52,782
- But TIA, right, M'Ed?
- TIA.

248
00:25:52,953 --> 00:25:54,181
What's TIA?

249
00:25:54,821 --> 00:25:58,723
- "This is Africa," huh?
- Right.

250
00:25:59,292 --> 00:26:01,760
- You want another?
- Sure.

251
00:26:05,565 --> 00:26:08,090
So which one are you?

252
00:26:09,569 --> 00:26:12,834
- Smuggler?
- Am I?

253
00:26:13,006 --> 00:26:15,941
Somehow you don't strike me
as the UNICEF type.

254
00:26:16,977 --> 00:26:18,945
How about soldier of fortune?

255
00:26:19,413 --> 00:26:21,973
Or is that too much of a cliché?

256
00:26:22,149 --> 00:26:23,480
Diamonds?

257
00:26:24,184 --> 00:26:27,779
- If I told you I was a missionary...?
- For Van De Kaap?

258
00:26:29,489 --> 00:26:32,083
Better watch that type of talk,
Miss Bowen.

259
00:26:32,259 --> 00:26:35,353
In America, it's bling-bling,
but out here, it's bling-bang, huh?

260
00:26:35,629 --> 00:26:38,757
I wouldn't want you
getting in any trouble.

261
00:26:40,033 --> 00:26:42,297
How much trouble
do you think I would get into...

262
00:26:42,469 --> 00:26:45,734
...for talking about blood diamonds?

263
00:26:48,542 --> 00:26:51,602
- You're a journalist.
- That's right.

264
00:26:55,549 --> 00:26:57,141
Piss off, huh?

265
00:27:01,488 --> 00:27:04,753
For five years, this country has reported
almost no diamond exports...

266
00:27:04,925 --> 00:27:08,588
...while Liberia, right next door,
has exported 2 billion dollars' worth.

267
00:27:08,762 --> 00:27:11,788
Very odd, considering that Liberia
has no diamonds to speak of.

268
00:27:11,965 --> 00:27:12,954
I'm shocked.

269
00:27:13,133 --> 00:27:16,466
Van De Kaap denies trading blood
diamonds, but admits it's impossible...

270
00:27:16,636 --> 00:27:20,970
...to tell where a diamond comes from
unless their smuggler gets caught.

271
00:27:21,141 --> 00:27:22,836
What do you want from me, huh?

272
00:27:23,009 --> 00:27:27,537
You know all about Van De Kaap.
Help me out. Off the record.

273
00:27:27,781 --> 00:27:32,241
Well, off the record, I like to get kissed
before I get fucked, huh?

274
00:27:34,821 --> 00:27:36,015
Shit.

275
00:28:09,356 --> 00:28:12,848
- Cordell. How is it, Shona?
- Long time, pal.

276
00:28:13,026 --> 00:28:16,393
- How's Alice?
- She's well, thanks.

277
00:28:16,563 --> 00:28:18,394
Tim must be in school, right?

278
00:28:18,565 --> 00:28:20,897
- Big kids, big problems, you know?
- Yeah, yeah.

279
00:28:21,067 --> 00:28:23,661
I heard you got into a spot of trouble
in the bush, huh?

280
00:28:23,837 --> 00:28:26,237
Well, you know the bush, right, bru?

281
00:28:27,007 --> 00:28:29,567
- Company doing well?
- Can't complain.

282
00:28:29,743 --> 00:28:32,371
Eleven wars in the continent.
We're keeping busy.

283
00:28:32,546 --> 00:28:34,980
So, what, you're here on holiday, huh?

284
00:28:36,683 --> 00:28:38,583
- How's the colonel?
- He sends his regards.

285
00:28:38,752 --> 00:28:42,449
Good, good. Score us a loose, huh?

286
00:28:43,557 --> 00:28:45,752
Smoking will kill you, bru.

287
00:28:46,026 --> 00:28:47,254
Only if I live, right?

288
00:28:52,599 --> 00:28:54,499
That's for breaking my TV, bru.

289
00:28:59,372 --> 00:29:02,899
Tell the colonel he'll get his money.
I'll come see him soon.

290
00:29:09,649 --> 00:29:10,877
Ten more.

291
00:29:11,051 --> 00:29:13,952
Come. Come.

292
00:29:20,060 --> 00:29:21,550
Go on.

293
00:29:35,742 --> 00:29:39,678
Dia. Dia. Come here.
Get away from there.

294
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:42,942
Go. Go, Mama.

295
00:29:43,116 --> 00:29:45,050
Stay down.

296
00:30:03,169 --> 00:30:04,830
Excuse me,
my name's Solomon Vandy--

297
00:30:05,005 --> 00:30:07,098
- Check the list.
- I have checked the list.

298
00:30:07,273 --> 00:30:11,733
- File papers at the Office for Refugees.
- Sir, I have filed papers with the office.

299
00:30:11,911 --> 00:30:13,902
Then God help you,
because I can't.

300
00:30:14,080 --> 00:30:15,138
- Please, sir--
- Next.

301
00:30:15,315 --> 00:30:17,442
- Sir-- Sir, no, please.
- Hey, hey. Me, me, me.

302
00:30:17,617 --> 00:30:21,383
Husband here. One year we look.

303
00:30:25,892 --> 00:30:28,053
Hurry, Mom. Go.

304
00:30:33,233 --> 00:30:34,598
Dia! Dia!

305
00:30:34,768 --> 00:30:35,757
- Jassie!
- Dia!

306
00:30:35,935 --> 00:30:37,527
- Mama!
- Dia!

307
00:30:37,704 --> 00:30:39,865
Jassie! Mama!

308
00:31:02,128 --> 00:31:04,961
He's been waiting.
What took you?

309
00:31:05,665 --> 00:31:09,032
What are you gonna do,
shoot me right here, huh, Shona?

310
00:31:09,202 --> 00:31:12,296
Now, don't be a wanker, man. Get in.

311
00:31:44,370 --> 00:31:46,770
- Hello, Danny.
- Colonel.

312
00:31:46,940 --> 00:31:48,737
You look well.

313
00:31:48,908 --> 00:31:52,071
Clean living and a pure heart,
I suppose, huh?

314
00:31:52,412 --> 00:31:54,107
Walk with me.

315
00:31:55,882 --> 00:31:58,715
It seems the rebels have taken back
the diamond fields, Danny.

316
00:31:58,885 --> 00:32:01,217
The government
of Sierra Leone has contracted us...

317
00:32:01,387 --> 00:32:03,355
...to go in there
and take the rebels down.

318
00:32:03,523 --> 00:32:05,115
So you sell the rebels weapons...

319
00:32:05,291 --> 00:32:07,953
...the government hires you
when they use them? Nice, sir.

320
00:32:08,428 --> 00:32:11,295
I assume you're asking
for mining concessions, huh?

321
00:32:11,464 --> 00:32:14,592
We save the government,
they show their gratitude.

322
00:32:14,768 --> 00:32:17,066
And you get rich, right?

323
00:32:21,374 --> 00:32:22,932
How long have I known you, Danny?

324
00:32:23,376 --> 00:32:26,539
I was... I was 19, sir.

325
00:32:26,780 --> 00:32:31,308
And you survived.
A lot of boys didn't. Why is that?

326
00:32:32,719 --> 00:32:35,381
Just lucky, I guess.

327
00:32:37,290 --> 00:32:42,159
No, you were a good soldier.
But I made you better, didn't I?

328
00:32:45,532 --> 00:32:46,965
Yes, sir. Yes, you did.

329
00:32:47,133 --> 00:32:50,159
And over the years,
didn't I protect you...

330
00:32:50,570 --> 00:32:54,529
...teach you about diamonds,
cut you in on the deals?

331
00:32:54,707 --> 00:32:58,370
- Some might call it that, yeah.
- But not you...

332
00:32:59,345 --> 00:33:03,008
...because you done with me now, eh?
On to bigger things.

333
00:33:06,152 --> 00:33:08,620
I need a man that knows
his way around up there.

334
00:33:08,788 --> 00:33:12,554
Unless, of course,
you wanna cut me in. Something pink?

335
00:33:13,626 --> 00:33:15,150
Sir...

336
00:33:15,328 --> 00:33:17,455
Our deal went bad,
and you owe me money.

337
00:33:17,630 --> 00:33:19,359
I'll take a stone as payment.

338
00:33:19,532 --> 00:33:23,400
Look, do you think if I found a stone
like that, I'd still be on this continent?

339
00:33:23,570 --> 00:33:27,404
- Come on.
- Danny, give me your hand.

340
00:33:30,410 --> 00:33:34,141
That's red earth. It's in our skin.

341
00:33:34,614 --> 00:33:37,014
The Shona say the color
comes from all the blood...

342
00:33:37,183 --> 00:33:39,743
...that's being spilled
fighting over the land.

343
00:33:41,788 --> 00:33:46,350
This is home.
You'll never leave Africa.

344
00:33:49,128 --> 00:33:51,790
If you say so, sir.

345
00:34:07,313 --> 00:34:10,942
So, what did you do, bury it?

346
00:34:12,151 --> 00:34:15,712
Yeah. Yeah, I would have
buried it, huh?

347
00:34:15,889 --> 00:34:19,916
- What are you talking about?
- What am I talking about? Come on, bru.

348
00:34:20,093 --> 00:34:21,526
I'm late for work.

349
00:34:21,694 --> 00:34:24,219
Pink, huh? The biggest one
he'd ever seen.

350
00:34:24,397 --> 00:34:26,524
You were in the mining camps,
weren't you, bru?

351
00:34:26,699 --> 00:34:30,191
Why else would that rebel with
the bandaged arm make up such a story?

352
00:34:30,370 --> 00:34:32,600
Go ask him.

353
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:48,148
Thank you.

354
00:34:57,797 --> 00:35:00,595
Your mothers and fathers,
your brothers and sisters are dead.

355
00:35:00,767 --> 00:35:02,632
- You are dead! You have been reborn.
- No!

356
00:35:02,802 --> 00:35:06,033
- We are your family now.
- No! No!

357
00:35:13,913 --> 00:35:16,245
Your parents are weak.

358
00:35:16,816 --> 00:35:21,253
They're the farmers.
They're the fishermen.

359
00:35:21,754 --> 00:35:25,315
They've done nothing
but suck the blood from this country.

360
00:35:26,693 --> 00:35:31,153
But you are the heroes
who will save this nation.

361
00:35:31,431 --> 00:35:33,399
You are not children anymore.

362
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:36,334
You're men.

363
00:35:38,538 --> 00:35:41,701
No one has ever given you respect...

364
00:35:41,874 --> 00:35:44,968
...but with this in your hand,
they go fear you.

365
00:35:45,144 --> 00:35:47,635
If you do not get
the respect you deserve...

366
00:35:47,814 --> 00:35:50,112
...you will take it
by shedding their blood.

367
00:35:50,283 --> 00:35:54,242
- Repeat after me, shed their blood.
- Shed their blood.

368
00:35:54,420 --> 00:35:57,480
- Louder! Shed their blood! Shed their blood!
- Shed their blood!

369
00:35:57,657 --> 00:36:00,785
Make them hear you in Freetown.
Shed their blood! Shed their blood!

370
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:03,520
Shed their blood! Shed their blood!
Shed their blood!

371
00:36:03,696 --> 00:36:06,597
- Dia Vandy, stand up.
- Shed their blood! Shed their blood!

372
00:36:06,766 --> 00:36:09,667
- Shed their blood! Shed their blood!
- Put your hand on the gun.

373
00:36:09,836 --> 00:36:11,428
Shed their blood!
Shed their blood!

374
00:36:11,604 --> 00:36:13,196
Shed their blood!
Shed their blood!

375
00:36:13,373 --> 00:36:16,399
- Shed their blood! Shed their blood!
- Now squeeze the trigger.

376
00:36:16,943 --> 00:36:21,346
Come on, Dia. Pull the trigger.
Pull the trigger!

377
00:36:55,481 --> 00:37:00,043
I know, I know.
It's hard to be a man.

378
00:37:00,787 --> 00:37:03,312
Sit up. Come.

379
00:37:03,489 --> 00:37:07,789
But you are a soldier
of the revolution now.

380
00:37:07,994 --> 00:37:10,861
And I am your commander.

381
00:37:11,364 --> 00:37:13,229
Whatever you need...

382
00:37:13,399 --> 00:37:16,630
...guns, CDs, food...

383
00:37:16,803 --> 00:37:20,466
...come to me.
I will take care of you.

384
00:37:23,776 --> 00:37:30,181
Today, you are promoted
to the rank of captain.

385
00:37:34,787 --> 00:37:36,778
Dia Vandy...

386
00:37:38,391 --> 00:37:40,222
...boss man.

387
00:37:57,977 --> 00:37:59,604
How's it, bru?

388
00:38:00,146 --> 00:38:03,309
- You got something for me, huh?
- Yeah.

389
00:38:04,083 --> 00:38:07,484
- So, what's new, M'Ed?
- Fucking RUF.

390
00:38:07,653 --> 00:38:10,178
Tried to hit the government building
across the street.

391
00:38:10,356 --> 00:38:15,020
Shit, man, half the people
be soldiers today, RUF tomorrow.

392
00:38:15,194 --> 00:38:18,595
- Might be time to get your family out, huh?
- And go where?

393
00:38:18,764 --> 00:38:22,495
Just fire up the chopper
and fly away like you people?

394
00:38:22,869 --> 00:38:24,700
This my country, man.

395
00:38:24,871 --> 00:38:28,329
We here long before you came,
long after you gone.

396
00:38:37,350 --> 00:38:40,513
- Hi. I'm Maddy Bowen.
- How about you dance with me?

397
00:38:40,686 --> 00:38:44,053
- No, I don't dance.
- Neither do I. Come on.

398
00:38:49,262 --> 00:38:51,662
- So, Danny...
- Archer.

399
00:38:51,964 --> 00:38:53,022
Archer.

400
00:38:54,033 --> 00:38:57,594
When did you first start
moving stones? Was it Angola?

401
00:38:59,372 --> 00:39:03,968
Then you did the whole
mercenary thing. Was that fun?

402
00:39:05,511 --> 00:39:09,174
So, what are you?
Nihilist? Opportunist?

403
00:39:09,382 --> 00:39:11,509
Maybe I wasn't breast-fed
as a child, huh?

404
00:39:13,653 --> 00:39:16,087
You think I haven't met
people like you before?

405
00:39:16,255 --> 00:39:19,622
- I think you get off on people like me.
- You think?

406
00:39:22,361 --> 00:39:24,886
When did you first start
working for Van De Kaap?

407
00:39:25,464 --> 00:39:27,091
Christ, you never stop, do you?

408
00:39:28,367 --> 00:39:31,734
No, I never stop.

409
00:39:32,438 --> 00:39:34,030
Do you want me to stop?

410
00:39:35,408 --> 00:39:39,310
Why don't we go back to your place,
see what's in the minibar, huh?

411
00:39:39,478 --> 00:39:41,571
I'm a print journalist. I drank it.

412
00:39:42,848 --> 00:39:45,578
Is it possible that you don't care
how many people die...

413
00:39:45,751 --> 00:39:47,651
...because of the deals you do?

414
00:39:47,820 --> 00:39:51,051
People here kill each other as a way of life.
Always been like that.

415
00:39:51,324 --> 00:39:54,157
So you can just watch it
and go about your day?

416
00:39:55,461 --> 00:39:57,554
Maybe we should all just
write about it, then.

417
00:39:57,730 --> 00:40:00,062
Look, thanks for the dance, huh?

418
00:40:02,268 --> 00:40:05,635
- And a shot too, huh, M'Ed?
- Sure.

419
00:40:09,475 --> 00:40:10,772
You're a hard case, huh?

420
00:40:10,943 --> 00:40:13,935
Tell me something,
how long you been here in Africa, huh?

421
00:40:14,146 --> 00:40:17,445
Three months. And before that,
Afghanistan and Bosnia.

422
00:40:17,750 --> 00:40:19,843
You come here
with your laptop computer...

423
00:40:20,019 --> 00:40:23,955
...and your malaria medicine
and your little bottles of hand sanitizer.

424
00:40:24,724 --> 00:40:27,750
Think you're gonna change
the outcome, huh?

425
00:40:27,927 --> 00:40:30,521
Let me tell you something.
You sell blood diamonds too.

426
00:40:30,696 --> 00:40:32,186
- Really?
- Yeah.

427
00:40:32,365 --> 00:40:33,354
Tell me, how is that?

428
00:40:33,532 --> 00:40:35,796
Who do you think buys
the stones that I bring out?

429
00:40:35,968 --> 00:40:39,597
Dreamy American girls who all want
a storybook wedding and a big, shiny rock...

430
00:40:39,772 --> 00:40:43,333
...like the ones in the advertisements
of your politically-correct magazines.

431
00:40:43,509 --> 00:40:46,501
So, please, don't come here
and make judgments on me, all right?

432
00:40:47,913 --> 00:40:52,213
I provide a service. The world wants what
we have, and they want it cheap.

433
00:40:52,385 --> 00:40:55,616
We're in business together.
Get over yourself, darling.

434
00:40:56,088 --> 00:41:00,184
Okay, just to clarify, not all American girls
want a storybook wedding...

435
00:41:00,359 --> 00:41:03,260
...just like not all Africans kill each other
as a way of life.

436
00:41:03,429 --> 00:41:05,829
And yeah, it's a shit, shit world,
but you know what?

437
00:41:05,998 --> 00:41:09,866
Good things are done every day,
just, apparently, not by you.

438
00:41:11,470 --> 00:41:14,496
This place is about to explode.

439
00:41:14,774 --> 00:41:16,799
I wanna spend my time
with someone else.

440
00:41:27,887 --> 00:41:30,913
You are listening to BBC World Service.

441
00:41:31,090 --> 00:41:34,821
In Sierra Leone, Revolutionary United Front
forces have been sighted...

442
00:41:34,994 --> 00:41:37,724
...within 10 kilometers
of the capital city of Freetown.

443
00:41:37,897 --> 00:41:40,559
The minister of the interior
has expressed confidence...

444
00:41:40,733 --> 00:41:43,099
...that the government troops
can repel the attack.

445
00:41:43,269 --> 00:41:46,534
All foreign nationals are being advised
to leave the country.

446
00:41:46,706 --> 00:41:48,867
There are also unconfirmed reports...

447
00:41:49,041 --> 00:41:53,102
...that atrocities are being committed by
both sides in the rapidly worsening situation.

448
00:41:53,279 --> 00:41:57,215
The United Nations has described
the refugee situation as critical.

449
00:42:08,794 --> 00:42:11,194
Don't tell me you're gonna try
and sell it yourself.

450
00:42:11,364 --> 00:42:13,889
To who?
And for what price, my friend?

451
00:42:14,066 --> 00:42:16,091
You need my help,
whether you like it or not.

452
00:42:16,268 --> 00:42:19,328
- What are you talking about?
- Here, let me help you with that.

453
00:42:19,505 --> 00:42:23,373
You hear that? You hear that?
They came into the city overnight.

454
00:42:23,542 --> 00:42:25,840
It's started.
What are you gonna do now, huh?

455
00:42:26,011 --> 00:42:30,311
Listen, the right stone can buy anything.
Information, safety, even freedom.

456
00:42:30,483 --> 00:42:32,917
But a big stone does not stay secret
for very long.

457
00:42:33,085 --> 00:42:36,350
The moment you tell anyone about it,
your life is absolutely worthless.

458
00:42:36,522 --> 00:42:39,650
The only reason you're alive is
you haven't told anyone where it is.

459
00:42:39,825 --> 00:42:41,087
Am I right? Am I?

460
00:42:41,494 --> 00:42:43,519
Who do you think got you
out of jail, huh?

461
00:42:43,696 --> 00:42:46,756
- That makes us partners.
- I am not your partner!

462
00:42:46,932 --> 00:42:49,423
What if I helped you find your family?

463
00:42:49,602 --> 00:42:51,126
What do you know of my family?

464
00:42:51,303 --> 00:42:54,329
The relief agencies are useless,
the hospitals are overwhelmed.

465
00:42:54,507 --> 00:42:57,101
- There are other ways, bru.
- Liar.

466
00:42:57,276 --> 00:43:00,507
Look at me. I know people, huh?
White people.

467
00:43:00,679 --> 00:43:03,807
Without me, you're just another
black man in Africa, all right?

468
00:43:07,186 --> 00:43:08,915
Oh, shit.

469
00:43:10,656 --> 00:43:12,248
We got no time.
What's it gonna be?

470
00:43:12,425 --> 00:43:14,416
You would say anything.
How can I trust you?

471
00:43:14,593 --> 00:43:17,994
I don't give a fuck about you, all right?
That diamond could be priceless!

472
00:43:18,164 --> 00:43:22,430
We split it, and you get your family.
What's it gonna be, yes or no? Yes or no?

473
00:43:22,601 --> 00:43:25,195
- Where will we go? Where do we go?
- Come on, follow me!

474
00:43:56,635 --> 00:43:58,262
Stay low!

475
00:44:00,139 --> 00:44:01,367
Get your ass over here!

476
00:44:12,418 --> 00:44:13,476
Wait!

477
00:44:13,919 --> 00:44:15,580
