--at this site.
Dozens of--

719
01:06:01,759 --> 01:06:03,693
Many are injured.

720
01:06:13,838 --> 01:06:17,001
Get back on the bus, huh?
Get back on! Come on!

721
01:06:17,175 --> 01:06:18,802
- Maddy!
- Move it! Move it!

722
01:06:18,976 --> 01:06:19,965
Get back on the bus!

723
01:06:20,144 --> 01:06:21,702
Solomon! Solomon!

724
01:06:21,879 --> 01:06:23,369
- Let's go.
- Solomon, come here!

725
01:06:23,548 --> 01:06:24,981
- Go, go, go.
- Come on, come on.

726
01:06:25,183 --> 01:06:27,845
- Get in the bus!
- Move, move, move! Come on, come on.

727
01:06:28,186 --> 01:06:30,017
- Move!
- Get in the bus. Let's go.

728
01:06:30,188 --> 01:06:32,383
Get in, get in.
Goddamn it, get in! Get in!

729
01:06:32,557 --> 01:06:34,991
- Let me inside!
- There's no fucking space!

730
01:06:35,159 --> 01:06:37,423
- Let them on the bus.
- You give him your seat.

731
01:06:37,595 --> 01:06:40,564
What if we just take your place, huh?
What if we take your place?

732
01:06:40,731 --> 01:06:43,666
That's enough. He can ride with me.
Oi, he can ride with me.

733
01:06:43,835 --> 01:06:46,395
Maddy! Let's go!
Maddy, let's go. Come on!

734
01:06:59,317 --> 01:07:02,445
Nothing like a little bang-bang
to get the heart started, Maddy.

735
01:07:03,321 --> 01:07:06,518
- Whatever you say, Corbauld.
- Come on, love. Don't be like that.

736
01:07:06,691 --> 01:07:10,149
Story's played out, hasn't it?
Government bad, rebels worse.

737
01:07:10,695 --> 01:07:13,129
No one gives a toss anymore.
Know what I mean?

738
01:07:48,900 --> 01:07:50,834
This medicine will make you strong...

739
01:07:51,369 --> 01:07:53,769
...make you invisible to your enemies.

740
01:07:53,938 --> 01:07:56,168
Bullets will bounce off you.

741
01:08:06,984 --> 01:08:10,750
Superboy Killer, yes, huh?
Commando.

742
01:08:11,923 --> 01:08:13,857
Foreigners are the cause of the problems.

743
01:08:16,460 --> 01:08:20,294
Poppy Sankoh say,
"Overthrow those who would exploit you."

744
01:08:22,166 --> 01:08:23,656
I am Baby Killer.

745
01:08:27,438 --> 01:08:31,101
- I am the Master of Disaster.
- You will be strong.

746
01:08:34,445 --> 01:08:35,878
I am Born Trouble.

747
01:08:42,286 --> 01:08:44,345
I am See Me No More.

748
01:08:53,898 --> 01:08:56,833
You'd think they'd want
at least one decent road in this place.

749
01:08:58,269 --> 01:09:02,399
I'm gonna have to start charging
an entrance fee. Oh, God!

750
01:09:33,219 --> 01:09:34,447
Get down!

751
01:09:42,562 --> 01:09:44,792
- Look out!
- Shit!

752
01:09:57,310 --> 01:09:58,868
- You all right?
- Fine.

753
01:10:04,517 --> 01:10:05,814
Shit!

754
01:10:08,922 --> 01:10:10,253
Hold on!

755
01:10:20,367 --> 01:10:21,766
Hold on!

756
01:10:33,046 --> 01:10:34,274
Come on.

757
01:10:41,788 --> 01:10:43,983
- Everyone all right, huh?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

758
01:10:44,190 --> 01:10:45,623
Let me see that. You okay?

759
01:10:45,792 --> 01:10:46,850
- Yeah.
- All right.

760
01:10:49,496 --> 01:10:52,488
Quietly, now. Quietly.

761
01:11:13,653 --> 01:11:15,086
Come on.

762
01:11:36,381 --> 01:11:40,545
Kamajors. Local militia
protecting their homes, huh?

763
01:11:40,719 --> 01:11:42,584
- Do not look them in the eye.
- No.

764
01:11:57,069 --> 01:11:58,559
Excuse me. Excuse me?

765
01:11:59,504 --> 01:12:02,871
Hi, I'm Maddy Bowen
with Vital Affairs magazine.

766
01:12:03,041 --> 01:12:06,101
Wonder if I could take your picture.
I'm just gonna get my camera.

767
01:12:06,278 --> 01:12:09,213
I've heard about your struggle.
I'd love to know more about it.

768
01:12:09,381 --> 01:12:12,009
Would you mind if I took your picture?
Everyone together?

769
01:12:12,351 --> 01:12:14,114
Everyone could all come in together.

770
01:12:17,623 --> 01:12:19,648
Is that okay?
If everyone could come closer.

771
01:12:20,692 --> 01:12:23,786
If you come over here and come in
nice and close. That's good.

772
01:12:23,962 --> 01:12:27,420
Yeah. That's great.
And we'll get one with all of us.

773
01:12:27,699 --> 01:12:29,496
There you go. That's perfect.

774
01:12:31,303 --> 01:12:33,828
How about one together?
Us together, what do you think?

775
01:12:34,006 --> 01:12:35,974
I'll come in like this, yeah?

776
01:12:36,775 --> 01:12:37,764
Cheese.

777
01:12:39,945 --> 01:12:42,277
So do you think
they've read your work?

778
01:12:42,447 --> 01:12:44,574
Shut up.

779
01:12:57,462 --> 01:12:59,794
Hey, get them, get them, get them.

780
01:13:01,433 --> 01:13:05,130
- I got a score. I got a score.
- You missed.

781
01:13:05,837 --> 01:13:07,998
Where have you come from?

782
01:13:08,573 --> 01:13:11,303
- Where did you come from?
- Where have you come from?

783
01:13:12,411 --> 01:13:15,244
That's right. Yeah.
From New York. From America.

784
01:13:15,414 --> 01:13:17,314
I don't have anything for you.

785
01:13:37,636 --> 01:13:39,433
My name is Benjamin Margai.

786
01:13:40,138 --> 01:13:42,197
Danny Archer. This is Maddy Bowen.

787
01:13:42,374 --> 01:13:45,434
- Hello. How are you?
- Very well, thank you.

788
01:14:00,258 --> 01:14:02,556
I'm the cameraman?

789
01:14:05,163 --> 01:14:08,098
The Belgians were the first
to chop off limbs in Africa.

790
01:14:08,266 --> 01:14:12,635
King Leopold took one hand
for every hundredth slave in the Congo...

791
01:14:12,804 --> 01:14:14,897
...to keep them in line.

792
01:14:15,540 --> 01:14:18,475
Many of these children
were taken by the RUF.

793
01:14:18,643 --> 01:14:20,634
We have taken them back.

794
01:14:20,812 --> 01:14:23,906
Some of them have been
made to do horrible things.

795
01:14:24,082 --> 01:14:27,108
We are trying
to bring them back to life.

796
01:14:27,285 --> 01:14:28,912
Let me show you.

797
01:14:30,956 --> 01:14:33,254
Imagine doing all this, huh?

798
01:14:34,559 --> 01:14:36,459
What's your excuse?

799
01:14:37,262 --> 01:14:42,598
Well, it's gotten hard to go back
to sipping lattes and talking interest rates.

800
01:14:42,834 --> 01:14:45,462
So you're an action junkie, huh?

801
01:14:46,405 --> 01:14:48,703
Three out of five ex-boyfriends
recently polled...

802
01:14:48,874 --> 01:14:53,311
...say that I prefer to be
in a constant state of crisis.

803
01:14:53,845 --> 01:14:56,109
Maybe I just give a shit.

804
01:14:59,785 --> 01:15:00,774
You were good today.

805
01:15:03,221 --> 01:15:04,552
You know that?

806
01:15:05,690 --> 01:15:07,180
You too.

807
01:15:10,128 --> 01:15:13,063
"--that sometimes they forgot
to close the door.

808
01:15:13,231 --> 01:15:16,291
She also wrote
about her sister Josie...

809
01:15:16,902 --> 01:15:21,896
...who was very ill
and who had to be taken to hospital."

810
01:15:23,942 --> 01:15:25,136
Cheers.

811
01:15:27,946 --> 01:15:30,540
So how many attacks
have there been in the area?

812
01:15:30,715 --> 01:15:33,616
I have known most of the rebels
since they were children.

813
01:15:33,785 --> 01:15:38,313
The local commander is still afraid
I will come after him with my ruler.

814
01:15:39,758 --> 01:15:43,216
So you think because your intentions
are good, they'll spare you, huh?

815
01:15:43,395 --> 01:15:46,228
My heart always told me
that people are inherently good.

816
01:15:46,398 --> 01:15:48,593
My experience suggests otherwise.

817
01:15:48,767 --> 01:15:50,564
But what about you, Mr. Archer?

818
01:15:51,002 --> 01:15:53,436
In your long career as a journalist...

819
01:15:53,605 --> 01:15:56,438
...would you say that people
are mostly good?

820
01:15:58,510 --> 01:15:59,943
No.

821
01:16:00,212 --> 01:16:01,736
I'd say they're just people.

822
01:16:01,913 --> 01:16:05,849
Exactly. It is what they do
that makes them good or bad.

823
01:16:06,017 --> 01:16:09,248
A moment of love,
even in a bad man...

824
01:16:09,521 --> 01:16:11,989
...can give meaning to a life.

825
01:16:12,157 --> 01:16:15,786
None of us knows which path
will lead us to God.

826
01:16:18,530 --> 01:16:20,020
Hey!

827
01:17:08,013 --> 01:17:09,878
It's palm wine.

828
01:17:19,157 --> 01:17:22,092
- Jesus Christ.
- Yeah, yeah. It takes getting used to, huh?

829
01:17:22,260 --> 01:17:23,750
God.

830
01:17:23,929 --> 01:17:26,659
- Drank that as a boy.
- In Rhodesia?

831
01:17:28,833 --> 01:17:30,061
I take notes.

832
01:17:32,771 --> 01:17:34,500
The Shona...

833
01:17:35,807 --> 01:17:38,105
The Shona have a word for me.

834
01:17:39,945 --> 01:17:43,574
- It means "white boy in Africa."
- When did you leave?

835
01:17:44,215 --> 01:17:45,910
I didn't leave.

836
01:17:46,084 --> 01:17:50,418
I got sent away to South Africa
in 1978 when the munts overran us.

837
01:17:50,755 --> 01:17:52,222
Then you joined the army?

838
01:17:55,093 --> 01:17:57,254
Yeah. Yeah, I did my time in Angola.

839
01:17:57,429 --> 01:18:00,125
- The 32 Battalion.
- That's right.

840
01:18:02,500 --> 01:18:05,765
You know, contrary to what
you might think about us...

841
01:18:05,937 --> 01:18:09,429
...we fought with the blacks, huh?
Yeah. Side by side.

842
01:18:09,608 --> 01:18:13,339
There was no apartheid in a foxhole.
The colonel always used to tell us that.

843
01:18:13,511 --> 01:18:16,912
- This is Colonel Coetzee?
- Yeah.

844
01:18:19,150 --> 01:18:22,551
Then, of course, it's 1994.
No more army.

845
01:18:22,721 --> 01:18:24,552
No more apartheid.

846
01:18:24,723 --> 01:18:28,090
Truth and reconciliation
and all of that rubbish, you know.

847
01:18:28,259 --> 01:18:29,749
Kumbaya.

848
01:18:30,528 --> 01:18:33,292
We fought and died together,
you know?

849
01:18:33,465 --> 01:18:36,730
Black and white. Most people back home
didn't even know we were at war.

850
01:18:36,901 --> 01:18:38,766
We thought we were
fighting Communism...

851
01:18:38,937 --> 01:18:42,805
...but in the end, it was all about
who gets what, you know?

852
01:18:42,974 --> 01:18:46,034
Ivory, oil, gold:

853
01:18:46,978 --> 01:18:48,741
Diamonds.

854
01:18:51,983 --> 01:18:54,952
So one day I decided,
"Fuck it," you know?

855
01:18:55,587 --> 01:18:57,145
"I'm gonna get mine."

856
01:18:57,322 --> 01:18:58,914
You gonna steal his diamond?

857
01:19:06,431 --> 01:19:10,128
That diamond is my ticket
out of this godforsaken continent.

858
01:19:10,335 --> 01:19:12,166
That doesn't answer the question.

859
01:19:22,814 --> 01:19:26,910
My dad came home
from the war in '69.

860
01:19:29,187 --> 01:19:31,052
And it took him...

861
01:19:32,190 --> 01:19:34,283
...about 20 years to get right.

862
01:19:36,161 --> 01:19:37,458
What?

863
01:19:40,331 --> 01:19:44,631
You Americans love to talk
about your feelings, huh?

864
01:19:44,803 --> 01:19:47,067
So, what does that mean?
What does that mean?

865
01:19:47,238 --> 01:19:49,365
- Got a thing for messed-up vets now?
- Shut up.

866
01:19:51,376 --> 01:19:52,843
You lost both your parents.

867
01:19:53,745 --> 01:19:56,578
That's a polite way
of putting it, yeah.

868
01:19:59,217 --> 01:20:01,549
Mom was raped and shot...

869
01:20:04,389 --> 01:20:07,483
...and Dad was decapitated
and hung from a hook in the barn.

870
01:20:09,027 --> 01:20:10,756
I was 9.

871
01:20:14,365 --> 01:20:15,957
Boohoo, right?

872
01:20:19,704 --> 01:20:21,831
Sometimes I wonder...

873
01:20:24,943 --> 01:20:28,003
...will God ever forgive us
for what we've done to each other?

874
01:20:31,649 --> 01:20:34,516
Then I look around and I realize...

875
01:20:35,420 --> 01:20:38,878
...God left this place a long time ago.

876
01:20:45,597 --> 01:20:47,622
It's...

877
01:20:49,901 --> 01:20:51,835
What's the point, huh?

878
01:21:35,280 --> 01:21:37,305
Oh, shit. Keep moving, huh?

879
01:21:37,482 --> 01:21:39,245
- What?
- Drive at them. They'll panic.

880
01:21:39,417 --> 01:21:41,681
Do you know where the word
"infantry" comes from?

881
01:21:41,853 --> 01:21:45,152
It means "child soldier."
They are just children.

882
01:21:45,323 --> 01:21:48,986
- Stop! Stop! RUF on the road!
- Hi. Hello. Hello.

883
01:21:50,228 --> 01:21:51,286
Hello, little brothers.

884
01:21:51,462 --> 01:21:53,987
- RUF on the road!
- Yeah, yeah. What is your names?

885
01:21:54,499 --> 01:21:56,797
I'm Dead Body.
Who is this motherfucker?

886
01:21:56,968 --> 01:21:58,629
We are teachers on our way to Kono.

887
01:21:58,803 --> 01:22:01,033
Only RUF on the road.

888
01:22:01,206 --> 01:22:03,140
- RUF only!
- Yes, yes, I understand that.

889
01:22:03,341 --> 01:22:04,672
- Only RUF!
- But son, this is--

890
01:22:06,945 --> 01:22:08,537
Don't move! Don't move! Fuck.

891
01:22:10,782 --> 01:22:14,115
Jesus Christ! Maddy, press your hand
against the exit wound there, huh?

892
01:22:14,285 --> 01:22:16,583
- Got it.
- Keep it there, huh?

893
01:22:16,754 --> 01:22:18,517
Whatever you do,
don't talk, all right?

894
01:22:18,690 --> 01:22:20,521
Is there any wine left in that jug?

895
01:22:20,692 --> 01:22:22,557
- Here.
- Pour it all over everything, huh?

896
01:22:24,095 --> 01:22:27,030
The colonel's gonna have a medic
at the airstrip in Kono.

897
01:22:27,198 --> 01:22:30,190
- How far is it?
- You said not to talk.

898
01:22:30,468 --> 01:22:31,662
A comedian, huh?

899
01:22:45,850 --> 01:22:48,250
- How's his pulse?
- I can feel it sometimes.

900
01:22:58,696 --> 01:23:01,665
- Hold it right there.
- Stop.

901
01:23:01,833 --> 01:23:03,061
Papers, please.

902
01:23:07,238 --> 01:23:08,466
Excuse me.

903
01:23:08,640 --> 01:23:11,575
I was just trying
to keep pressure on the wound.

904
01:23:11,743 --> 01:23:14,268
- He's lost a lot of blood.
- You'll be all right, huh?

905
01:23:14,946 --> 01:23:16,243
Will you?

906
01:23:16,948 --> 01:23:19,940
I'll check on him in the tent
in a little bit. Thank you.

907
01:23:20,184 --> 01:23:21,515
Hey.

908
01:23:22,053 --> 01:23:24,044
Look who's alive, eh?

909
01:23:24,222 --> 01:23:25,553
I told the H you'd be back.

910
01:23:27,525 --> 01:23:30,460
I'm afraid we're evacuating
all non-military personnel, miss.

911
01:23:30,628 --> 01:23:32,459
Transport touches down at 1600.

912
01:23:32,630 --> 01:23:34,393
She's with me, all right?

913
01:23:34,599 --> 01:23:38,262
No exceptions, pal. This is gonna be ugly.
Colonel doesn't want an audience.

914
01:23:38,436 --> 01:23:41,234
Is I.R.'s presence here
known to other African nations?

915
01:23:42,740 --> 01:23:44,765
- She's with you?
- Yeah.

916
01:23:45,910 --> 01:23:47,775
Come on. The colonel's this way.

917
01:23:47,946 --> 01:23:49,777
Give me a minute, huh?

918
01:23:52,951 --> 01:23:55,476
We block their escape
by blowing the bridge.

919
01:23:57,121 --> 01:23:58,816
That's correct.

920
01:23:59,557 --> 01:24:01,855
You made it out. Well done.

921
01:24:02,060 --> 01:24:03,994
Negative, Kilo Foxtrot, stand by.

922
01:24:04,662 --> 01:24:08,325
- Colonel, sir.
- So must be real, then.

923
01:24:09,500 --> 01:24:10,694
The pink.

924
01:24:11,202 --> 01:24:13,796
Well, you're part
of this operation now.

925
01:24:13,972 --> 01:24:17,464
First we snuff everything that moves
out there, then we find your diamond.

926
01:24:17,642 --> 01:24:19,269
Colonel?

927
01:24:19,811 --> 01:24:22,245
Go get kitted. Yes?

928
01:24:28,553 --> 01:24:30,544
Move, move, move!

929
01:24:30,755 --> 01:24:34,020
- Go get your kit.
- Will do, chum. Will do.

930
01:24:37,562 --> 01:24:40,725
It's go time, all right?
Meet me behind the tents.

931
01:24:43,835 --> 01:24:45,530
How's Benjamin?

932
01:24:45,703 --> 01:24:47,170
They say he'll live.

933
01:24:48,506 --> 01:24:49,768
Good. Good.

934
01:24:57,181 --> 01:24:58,978
Listen, Maddy...

935
01:25:00,385 --> 01:25:02,148
...I need you to do me one last favor.

936
01:25:03,187 --> 01:25:04,552
Yeah?

937
01:25:06,524 --> 01:25:08,185
Tell that guard
you wanna put him...

938
01:25:08,359 --> 01:25:11,021
...on the cover of Soldier of Fortune
magazine for me.

939
01:25:17,068 --> 01:25:18,296
You're going in.

940
01:25:22,707 --> 01:25:24,971
You and Solomon.

941
01:25:27,145 --> 01:25:28,134
You're going in now.

942
01:25:28,980 --> 01:25:31,175
Your plane leaves
in a few minutes, huh?

943
01:25:33,785 --> 01:25:35,753
You're an idiot.

944
01:25:40,058 --> 01:25:42,925
- What if I wanted to go in with you?
- I'd say no.

945
01:25:43,094 --> 01:25:45,085
- What if I insist?
- I'd insist back.

946
01:25:51,202 --> 01:25:52,396
It's my story.

947
01:25:52,570 --> 01:25:55,971
Your story is Van De Kaap, all right?
That stone is mine.

948
01:25:56,140 --> 01:25:59,576
I'm not leaving here without it,
you understand?

949
01:26:01,045 --> 01:26:03,912
Please, just give me two minutes.

950
01:26:20,665 --> 01:26:22,064
Yeah.

951
01:26:33,377 --> 01:26:35,072
- Hello.
- Hi.

952
01:26:35,246 --> 01:26:38,477
My name is Maddy Bowen.
I'm with Vital Affairs magazine.

953
01:26:38,649 --> 01:26:41,117
I was wondering
if I could ask you a few questions.

954
01:26:41,285 --> 01:26:42,809
Well, that depends what they are.

955
01:26:42,987 --> 01:26:46,946
Oh, I see you're familiar
with our devious ways, aren't you?

956
01:26:47,692 --> 01:26:49,592
Okay, so I'll start
with something simple.

957
01:27:02,206 --> 01:27:04,868
And before that you were with
the South African Defense--?

958
01:27:05,042 --> 01:27:06,703
- Defense Force, correct.
- Of course.

959
01:27:06,878 --> 01:27:10,314
And was that with Colonel Coetzee?
Were you in Angola?

960
01:27:10,481 --> 01:27:12,005
Angola, yeah.

961
01:27:13,618 --> 01:27:16,587
That is all I really need to know.
Thank you so much.

962
01:27:16,787 --> 01:27:18,254
- Thank you.
- Okay.

963
01:27:28,266 --> 01:27:29,665
Thank you, huh?

964
01:27:29,834 --> 01:27:32,268
Just keeping my end of the deal.

965
01:27:32,870 --> 01:27:34,167
Good luck to you, Solomon.

966
01:27:34,472 --> 01:27:35,962
Okay.

967
01:27:37,141 --> 01:27:40,975
- I hope you find what you're looking for.
- Thank you for all you have done.

968
01:27:48,419 --> 01:27:51,013
- Listen, I--
- No, you listen.

969
01:27:55,626 --> 01:27:57,526
In another life maybe, all right?

970
01:27:58,963 --> 01:28:00,794
Yeah. Sure.

971
01:28:00,965 --> 01:28:02,330
Yeah.

972
01:28:06,671 --> 01:28:08,798
You find yourself a good man,
all right, Maddy?

973
01:28:14,745 --> 01:28:17,771
You know, I've got three sisters.

974
01:28:17,949 --> 01:28:20,577
They're all married to good men.

975
01:28:22,453 --> 01:28:23,511
I prefer my life.

976
01:28:26,157 --> 01:28:30,617
Here is my office phone...

977
01:28:30,795 --> 01:28:33,161
...home phone, cellphone.

978
01:28:35,266 --> 01:28:38,429
I'm used to being pursued,
but what the heck.

979
01:28:49,614 --> 01:28:51,741
You better get on that plane, huh?

980
01:28:53,484 --> 01:28:55,384
You should get on that plane.

981
01:29:03,561 --> 01:29:05,358
So should you.

982
01:29:11,836 --> 01:29:12,962
You gonna call me?

983
01:29:16,774 --> 01:29:18,264
Soon as I'm near a phone, yeah.

984
01:29:19,210 --> 01:29:21,576
Yeah, right.

985
01:29:43,401 --> 01:29:46,666
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

986
01:29:51,242 --> 01:29:52,834
Oh, shit.

987
01:29:53,110 --> 01:29:55,840
Nabil? Yeah, I'll call you
when we get closer, all right?

988
01:29:56,013 --> 01:29:58,607
You keep me posted. Right.

989
01:29:58,783 --> 01:30:02,583
All right. I set the pace, huh?
Two-hour marches, five-minute breaks.

990
01:30:02,753 --> 01:30:06,587
If I hold my hand up like this, you stop.
If I point to the dirt, you lie flat.

991
01:30:06,757 --> 01:30:10,318
If I say go, you move like your life
depended on it. Understood?

992
01:30:10,494 --> 01:30:13,156
- Yes, boss.
- Come on.

993
01:30:23,441 --> 01:30:25,102
Tell me about the stone.

994
01:30:25,276 --> 01:30:27,904
Is it clear or is it milky?

995
01:30:28,079 --> 01:30:29,603
Clear.

996
01:30:29,780 --> 01:30:32,180
And the color, is it strong?

997
01:30:32,350 --> 01:30:33,578
Does it hold the light?

998
01:30:33,751 --> 01:30:35,810
It is as you say.

999
01:30:36,253 --> 01:30:39,416
- About the size of a bird's egg?
- Yes.

1000
01:30:39,590 --> 01:30:43,754
One hundred carats.
Come on, let's pick up the pace.

1001
01:31:25,336 --> 01:31:26,701
Dia!

1002
01:31:28,606 --> 01:31:30,574
Stop the truck!

1003
01:31:31,342 --> 01:31:33,037
I thought it was Dia.

1004
01:32:26,964 --> 01:32:28,522
Wake up.

1005
01:32:30,367 --> 01:32:33,461
Don't worry, they're gone, huh?

1006
01:32:34,805 --> 01:32:37,933
You know, I once had this buddy...

1007
01:32:38,108 --> 01:32:39,973
...named Mabhoko.

1008
01:32:40,744 --> 01:32:43,975
We used to hunt bush meat
together as kids, huh?

1009
01:32:44,782 --> 01:32:46,147
Baboons.

1010
01:32:46,317 --> 01:32:49,184
Baboons, they were
the hardest to catch. They're...

1011
01:32:50,287 --> 01:32:51,618
They're cunning.

1012
01:32:51,789 --> 01:32:53,882
Cunning creatures.

1013
01:32:54,158 --> 01:32:56,786
Fast, strong.

1014
01:32:56,961 --> 01:32:59,191
Got good eyesight.

1015
01:32:59,697 --> 01:33:03,724
We would always find them
by the smell of their shit.

1016
01:33:03,901 --> 01:33:09,032
And that's how we learned to track
your black terrorists in Angola, huh?

1017
01:33:13,110 --> 01:33:14,543
By the smell of your shit.

1018
01:33:15,579 --> 01:33:17,046
It's not...

1019
01:33:17,214 --> 01:33:19,944
It's not the same as a baboon's.

1020
01:33:22,186 --> 01:33:25,747
But, you know, after you skin it...

1021
01:33:27,057 --> 01:33:29,287
...the flesh of a baboon...

1022
01:33:29,560 --> 01:33:31,960
...isn't that much different
than a man's, you know.

1023
01:33:35,366 --> 01:33:39,302
I'll tell you, I can track anything.

1024
01:33:51,549 --> 01:33:53,710
You risk my life like that again...

1025
01:33:59,089 --> 01:34:01,216
...and I'll peel your face
back off your head.

1026
01:34:03,727 --> 01:34:05,991
Do you understand?

1027
01:34:14,238 --> 01:34:16,297
Make us a fire.

1028
01:35:26,577 --> 01:35:28,169
What'd he say?

1029
01:35:28,345 --> 01:35:30,472
We are going the right way.

1030
01:35:37,621 --> 01:35:40,351
Hold up there, my man.
It's this way, huh?

1031
01:35:41,825 --> 01:35:44,020
Where do you think you are going?

1032
01:35:45,696 --> 01:35:47,357
Stop!

1033
01:35:47,631 --> 01:35:49,326
I said, stop!

1034
01:35:49,767 --> 01:35:51,325
He is not down there, all right?

1035
01:35:53,370 --> 01:35:57,033
All right. You're gonna need
some of that old discipline, huh?

1036
01:35:57,207 --> 01:35:59,471
Now you listen here, my boy,
and you listen well.

1037
01:35:59,643 --> 01:36:01,611
You are not going down there.
Are we clear?

1038
01:36:01,779 --> 01:36:03,406
You are not the master.

1039
01:36:03,580 --> 01:36:07,209
Right now, that is exactly what I am,
and you'd better remember it, Kaffir!

1040
01:36:22,366 --> 01:36:23,697
Don't you fucking move, huh?

1041
01:36:23,867 --> 01:36:25,835
Don't you move. Don't you move, huh?

1042
01:36:26,003 --> 01:36:28,335
- My son is there!
- Your son is gone!

1043
01:36:28,505 --> 01:36:29,836
- He is alive!
- He's gone!

1044
01:36:30,007 --> 01:36:32,567
He's alive! He's there
with those crazy people!

1045
01:36:33,777 --> 01:36:37,213
I am his father! His father!
I should have protected him!

1046
01:36:37,681 --> 01:36:41,583
I must go find him.
I cannot live without knowing!

1047
01:36:41,752 --> 01:36:43,982
Shoot me if you want, but I'm going.

1048
01:36:46,090 --> 01:36:49,548
Why should it matter,
I'm dead already.

1049
01:36:57,401 --> 01:36:59,665
We wait until dark, huh?

1050
01:37:28,832 --> 01:37:30,231
Are you satisfied?

1051
01:37:33,203 --> 01:37:35,728
All right, come on.

1052
01:37:40,477 --> 01:37:42,672
--is fighting for Sierra Leone

1053
01:37:42,846 --> 01:37:45,906
RUF is fighting for Sierra Leone

1054
01:37:46,083 --> 01:37:49,018
Go tell my parents
They may see me no more

1055
01:37:49,186 --> 01:37:52,246
In the battlefield
We're fighting forever

1056
01:37:52,422 --> 01:37:55,323
Go tell my parents
They may see me no more

1057
01:37:55,492 --> 01:37:56,959
In the battlefield...

1058
01:37:59,530 --> 01:38:01,498
You are how old?

1059
01:38:01,665 --> 01:38:03,428
Me? I'm 31.

1060
01:38:03,600 --> 01:38:05,761
And you have no wife?

1061
01:38:06,236 --> 01:38:09,103
- No.
- No children?

1062
01:38:10,274 --> 01:38:11,571
No.

1063
01:38:11,742 --> 01:38:13,369
And no home?

1064
01:38:13,544 --> 01:38:15,205
No.

1065
01:38:15,913 --> 01:38:18,313
But you have money, yes?

1066
01:38:18,482 --> 01:38:20,746
Yeah, some.

1067
01:38:20,918 --> 01:38:22,909
But not enough?

1068
01:38:25,422 --> 01:38:26,980
No.

1069
01:38:27,724 --> 01:38:32,218
If you get this diamond,
you will have enough money, yes?

1070
01:38:34,364 --> 01:38:35,388
Yes.

1071
01:38:35,566 --> 01:38:38,364
Then you will get
a wife and children?

1072
01:38:38,535 --> 01:38:39,934
Probably not, no.

1073
01:38:42,005 --> 01:38:42,994
What?

1074
01:38:45,108 --> 01:38:46,632
What?

1075
01:38:47,044 --> 01:38:49,103
I am confused.

1076
01:38:50,180 --> 01:38:51,647
Yeah?

1077
01:38:51,815 --> 01:38:54,613
That makes two of us, my bru.

1078
01:38:57,120 --> 01:39:00,612
Oh, Christ.
I've gotta quit smoking, huh?

1079
01:39:01,225 --> 01:39:03,193
Why don't you?

1080
01:39:03,460 --> 01:39:05,860
I'll tell you what, Solomon.

1081
01:39:06,129 --> 01:39:10,657
You find me this diamond,
and I'll quit right then and there, huh?

1082
01:39:18,075 --> 01:39:21,067
- You were born in Zimbabwe?
- Oh, yeah.

1083
01:39:21,245 --> 01:39:24,408
- Is it beautiful there?
- Sure you're not a reporter?

1084
01:39:24,815 --> 01:39:28,273
Because you ask a hell of a lot
of questions, my man.

1085
01:39:35,926 --> 01:39:39,623
My grandfather told
many stories of war.

1086
01:39:39,863 --> 01:39:42,696
How the Mende fought the Temne.

1087
01:39:42,866 --> 01:39:46,597
Or how two tribes would fight
when somebody had stolen a woman.

1088
01:39:56,680 --> 01:40:00,047
I understand white people
want our diamonds, yes?

1089
01:40:03,086 --> 01:40:06,817
But how can my own people
do this to each other?

1090
01:40:15,098 --> 01:40:17,157
I know good people...

1091
01:40:17,334 --> 01:40:20,201
...who say there is something
wrong with us...

1092
01:40:20,570 --> 01:40:21,730
...inside our black skin.

1093
01:40:21,905 --> 01:40:25,238
That we were better off
when the white man ruled.

1094
01:40:27,144 --> 01:40:29,942
But my son is good.

1095
01:40:31,515 --> 01:40:33,710
And when he grows up...

1096
01:40:33,884 --> 01:40:35,112
...and peace comes...

1097
01:40:39,122 --> 01:40:41,784
...this place will be a paradise.

1098
01:40:49,666 --> 01:40:52,134
We'll get your son back, huh?

1099
01:41:33,844 --> 01:41:36,176
Where is it exactly?

1100
01:41:37,714 --> 01:41:40,615
Through the camp, by the river.

1101
01:41:45,222 --> 01:41:46,917
Christ.

1102
01:41:47,391 --> 01:41:49,018
Okay.

1103
01:41:49,659 --> 01:41:51,524
I'm gonna make contact
with the colonel.

1104
01:41:51,695 --> 01:41:53,219
He'll send in an air strike.

1105
01:41:53,663 --> 01:41:56,632
- What is that?
- A chopper, huh? An attack helicopter.

1106
01:41:56,800 --> 01:41:59,325
- We use it as a diversion.
- What if my son is there?

1107
01:41:59,503 --> 01:42:00,800
- He isn't.
- How do you know?

1108
01:42:00,971 --> 01:42:04,566
I said we do it my way now, all right?
Don't fuck with me.

1109
01:42:14,484 --> 01:42:16,884
Cordell, it's Danny.

1110
01:42:17,054 --> 01:42:19,386
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Shut up and listen, all right?

1111
01:42:19,556 --> 01:42:22,423
You tell the colonel I've found the stone.

1112
01:42:22,592 --> 01:42:25,561
No, I haven't got it in my hands,
but I'm OP'ing its location.

1113
01:42:25,729 --> 01:42:27,321
It's a major rebel camp, my man.

1114
01:42:27,497 --> 01:42:29,863
You tell him to send in the dakadak.

1115
01:42:30,434 --> 01:42:33,301
Because I stole a GPS, that's how.

1116
01:42:33,470 --> 01:42:36,030
If you shut up and listen,
I could give the coordinates.

1117
01:42:36,473 --> 01:42:39,499
Zero-nine-zero-five-four-two-four, north.

1118
01:42:39,676 --> 01:42:44,238
Three-two-seven-two-nine
three-zero-five-zero, east.

1119
01:42:44,414 --> 01:42:46,678
I'll call back at midnight to confirm.

1120
01:42:49,453 --> 01:42:52,388
You can look all night,
my friend, right?

1121
01:42:52,556 --> 01:42:55,218
I promise you he is not there.

1122
01:43:00,464 --> 01:43:02,659
They're coming in the morning, all right?

1123
01:43:02,833 --> 01:43:05,267
No movement, my friend. You stay still.

1124
01:43:07,204 --> 01:43:09,638
When it gets dark,
then we move in closer.

1125
01:43:31,795 --> 01:43:34,787
Solomon. Shit.

1126
01:43:45,575 --> 01:43:46,974
I can do it.

1127
01:43:47,144 --> 01:43:48,236
- Help me.
- Help him.

1128
01:43:48,411 --> 01:43:50,470
Thank you, Papa.

1129
01:44:32,422 --> 01:44:34,652
Hey, you smell.

1130
01:44:35,859 --> 01:44:37,326
That's fine.

1131
01:44:49,639 --> 01:44:51,607
- Ready? I'm winning.
- Okay, let's go.

1132
01:44:51,775 --> 01:44:53,436
Play, man.

1133
01:44:55,011 --> 01:44:57,912
- Play. Play the card.
- Play.

1134
01:45:24,708 --> 01:45:25,834
Dia.

1135
01:45:28,878 --> 01:45:30,573
Leave me alone.

1136
01:45:31,615 --> 01:45:34,846
- Dia. I'm your papa. Come with me.
- Hey.

1137
01:45:35,018 --> 01:45:36,747
- Dia.
- Get away from me.

1138
01:45:36,920 --> 01:45:38,717
- Dia. Dia!
- I do not know you. Traitor!

1139
01:45:39,089 --> 01:45:41,580
- Enemy! Enemy!
- What the hell are you doing?

1140
01:45:41,758 --> 01:45:42,986
- What are you doing?
- I don't know you!

1141
01:45:43,159 --> 01:45:44,456
- What's wrong?
- I hate you!

1142
01:45:44,628 --> 01:45:46,357
- Dia, come with me!
- I hate you!

1143
01:45:46,529 --> 01:45:48,053
Get away from me!

1144
01:45:50,533 --> 01:45:52,398
- Get him!
- Don't shoot!

1145
01:45:52,902 --> 01:45:55,132
- Don't shoot! Don't--! Don't shoot!
- I hate you!

1146
01:45:55,305 --> 01:45:57,205
- Fisherman! Traitor!
- Don't shoot!

1147
01:45:57,374 --> 01:45:59,604
Get away from me!

1148
01:46:06,716 --> 01:46:08,877
I knew you would come back.

1149
01:46:09,352 --> 01:46:12,844
I have dug and dug and dug,
but I've found nothing.

1150
01:46:13,023 --> 01:46:14,923
Nothing.

1151
01:46:15,191 --> 01:46:16,681
Dig, dig, dig!

1152
01:46:16,860 --> 01:46:19,158
You will find it for me.

1153
01:46:20,130 --> 01:46:22,428
You will dig up
what you have come back for.

1154
01:46:22,599 --> 01:46:23,623
No.

1155
01:46:23,800 --> 01:46:26,234
Why should the diamond
go to the foreign devils?

1156
01:46:26,970 --> 01:46:30,235
We will use it
to make the country strong.

1157
01:46:30,707 --> 01:46:33,301
RUF is fighting for the people!

1158
01:46:35,645 --> 01:46:38,739
RUF is fighting for Sierra Leone!

1159
01:46:41,584 --> 01:46:43,313
Pick it up.

1160
01:46:44,521 --> 01:46:47,490
Why? You are going to kill me anyway.

1161
01:46:47,657 --> 01:46:50,751
I do not need to kill you,
Solomon Vandy.

1162
01:46:53,596 --> 01:46:55,791
If you do not bring me the diamond...

1163
01:46:55,965 --> 01:46:58,195
...I will find the rest of your family.

1164
01:46:58,368 --> 01:47:00,802
Just as I have found your son.

1165
01:47:01,905 --> 01:47:05,272
I will rape your wife
in front of your eyes...

1166
01:47:06,076 --> 01:47:08,374
...slit her throat...

1167
01:47:08,978 --> 01:47:11,344
...and I will keep your daughters
for myself.

1168
01:47:16,753 --> 01:47:19,187
You think I am a devil...

1169
01:47:19,356 --> 01:47:21,688
...but only because I have lived in hell.

1170
01:47:23,326 --> 01:47:25,988
I want to get out.

1171
01:47:26,596 --> 01:47:28,689
You will help me.

1172
01:47:31,534 --> 01:47:32,831
I don't remember.

1173
01:47:33,002 --> 01:47:35,971
Find it or your family will die!

1174
01:47:36,906 --> 01:47:38,771
Now pick it up!

1175
01:47:54,324 --> 01:47:55,757
- Go!
- Bastards!

1176
01:47:55,925 --> 01:47:57,290
Shoot it!

1177
01:48:02,265 --> 01:48:03,254
Dia!

1178
01:48:15,345 --> 01:48:17,540
Come, boy. Come. This way. This way.

1179
01:48:18,415 --> 01:48:19,643
Dia!

1180
01:48:42,539 --> 01:48:44,131
Colonel, we think Archer's there.

1181
01:48:44,307 --> 01:48:47,140
I don't give a damn who's down there.
Kill them all.

1182
01:48:57,487 --> 01:48:58,749
Dia!

1183
01:49:13,503 --> 01:49:14,800
I'm coming!

1184
01:49:18,341 --> 01:49:20,002
- Dia!
- Bastard!

1185
01:49:43,166 --> 01:49:44,531
No!

1186
01:50:04,621 --> 01:50:05,952
Dia!

1187
01:51:12,188 --> 01:51:15,123
- We found his digger, sir.
- Keep him close.

1188
01:51:17,093 --> 01:51:19,288
- Danny boy.
- Colonel.

1189
01:51:19,462 --> 01:51:22,829
- Thanks for calling it in.
- Yeah, yeah. Always happy to help, huh?

1190
01:51:22,999 --> 01:51:26,332
So where is it? The stone?

1191
01:51:26,502 --> 01:51:28,436
We split, huh? Fifty-fifty, all right?

1192
01:51:28,605 --> 01:51:30,232
Look around you, Danny boy.

1193
01:51:30,406 --> 01:51:33,375
You're not in a position
to be dictating terms.

1194
01:51:33,543 --> 01:51:35,636
Then you will never find it, sir.

1195
01:51:35,812 --> 01:51:37,439
That's correct.

1196
01:51:39,115 --> 01:51:41,743
- But he will.
- Come. Up.

1197
01:51:43,386 --> 01:51:45,616
Introduce me to your digger.

1198
01:51:47,190 --> 01:51:48,851
Solomon Vandy.

1199
01:51:49,025 --> 01:51:51,186
This is Colonel Coetzee.
He wants the diamond.

1200
01:51:51,361 --> 01:51:54,387
- No more than you.
- Fuck.

1201
01:51:54,564 --> 01:51:56,555
You gonna show us where it's hidden?

1202
01:51:59,235 --> 01:52:00,930
Does he speak English?

1203
01:52:01,104 --> 01:52:04,130
He will only tell me, sir.
I promise you that.

1204
01:52:04,974 --> 01:52:08,034
- Let me talk to him, huh?
- Go on.

1205
01:52:14,784 --> 01:52:17,150
All right, my friend.

1206
01:52:17,320 --> 01:52:19,254
End of the line here, huh?

1207
01:52:19,422 --> 01:52:22,687
- You just tell him where it is, all right?
- I do not trust him.

1208
01:52:22,859 --> 01:52:26,295
I don't trust him either,
but we haven't got much of a choice here.

1209
01:52:27,997 --> 01:52:31,125
I promise you
he will shoot us both in the head.

1210
01:52:31,567 --> 01:52:34,331
Right, tell him, huh?
Tell him where it is, huh?

1211
01:52:34,504 --> 01:52:37,098
- Go on. Come on.
- I'm not feeling the love, Danny.

1212
01:52:38,307 --> 01:52:41,140
All right.
No more messing about, all right?

1213
01:52:41,310 --> 01:52:44,302
I said tell him where it is!
Tell him where it is! Now!

1214
01:52:44,480 --> 01:52:46,141
Tell him!

1215
01:52:47,316 --> 01:52:49,113
- No.
- Fucking--

1216
01:52:49,285 --> 01:52:51,981
Danny, there are other ways
to do this, okay?

1217
01:52:52,155 --> 01:52:53,782
Yeah, yeah.

1218
01:53:01,964 --> 01:53:04,956
- If he tells us, do we have a deal, sir?
- Seventy-thirty.

1219
01:53:05,134 --> 01:53:07,534
Sixty-forty. I've already lined up a buyer.

1220
01:53:07,704 --> 01:53:09,365
Agreed.

1221
01:53:14,544 --> 01:53:16,102
Come here.

1222
01:53:18,681 --> 01:53:22,117
This is his son. Vandy will do
whatever you want for his sake, all right?

1223
01:53:22,285 --> 01:53:27,052
Danny, you're a pisser, man. Well done.
Boys, we move out.

1224
01:53:29,826 --> 01:53:32,124
What do you say, Mr. Vandy?

1225
01:53:32,595 --> 01:53:35,496
- You ready to take a walk?
- Come on.

1226
01:53:41,771 --> 01:53:43,363
Come on.

1227
01:53:56,319 --> 01:53:59,413
So who's the buyer?
I'm guessing London.

1228
01:53:59,622 --> 01:54:02,887
Well, they no longer accept
conflict diamonds, huh?

1229
01:54:03,059 --> 01:54:05,527
Wouldn't hurt to interest
some other parties.

1230
01:54:06,062 --> 01:54:09,054
- Start a bidding war.
- What, one war's not enough for you, huh?

1231
01:54:09,999 --> 01:54:11,694
I missed you, Danny.

1232
01:54:12,001 --> 01:54:16,165
See? It is here.
He has tried to find it.

1233
01:54:16,339 --> 01:54:19,035
All right, Mr. Vandy.
Time for you to start digging.

1234
01:54:34,090 --> 01:54:36,354
Hey, boet, have you got a smoke?

1235
01:54:36,826 --> 01:54:38,726
Smoking will kill you.

1236
01:54:39,495 --> 01:54:40,985
Sorry.

1237
01:54:44,066 --> 01:54:45,966
It's all right.

1238
01:54:46,135 --> 01:54:48,262
Time I quit smoking anyway,
huh, Solomon?

1239
01:55:02,785 --> 01:55:04,116
- It's gone.
- What?

1240
01:55:04,287 --> 01:55:06,380
Someone has taken it.

1241
01:55:07,490 --> 01:55:11,256
This is where I buried it.
It isn't here.

1242
01:55:11,727 --> 01:55:15,094
Well, then there's no reason
for any of you to stay alive. Is there?

1243
01:55:19,435 --> 01:55:21,096
Wait, wait, wait.

1244
01:55:21,270 --> 01:55:23,500
I know, I know. I know where it is.

1245
01:55:23,973 --> 01:55:25,964
- I know where it is.
- It better be there.

1246
01:55:31,147 --> 01:55:32,136
Yes.

1247
01:55:32,315 --> 01:55:35,682
Oh, here, here.
It is here.

1248
01:55:35,852 --> 01:55:37,513
- Yeah? Yeah, there it is.
- Yes.

1249
01:55:38,688 --> 01:55:40,087
Fuck!

1250
01:55:58,741 --> 01:56:00,675
TIA, huh, Danny?

1251
01:56:02,078 --> 01:56:03,670
TIA.

1252
01:56:10,586 --> 01:56:14,044
Keep digging, huh?
They'll be here any second. Come on.

1253
01:56:16,259 --> 01:56:17,521
Keep digging.

1254
01:56:30,373 --> 01:56:33,103
- It had better be there, huh?
- Yes, yes.

1255
01:56:36,145 --> 01:56:37,737
Have you got it?

1256
01:56:39,181 --> 01:56:42,446
- Have you got it, huh?
- Yes, got it. Oh, yes.

1257
01:56:43,886 --> 01:56:45,148
Oh, yes.

1258
01:56:47,323 --> 01:56:48,915
Solomon.

1259
01:56:55,731 --> 01:56:58,700
Dia, what are you doing?

1260
01:56:59,201 --> 01:57:00,691
Dia.

1261
01:57:03,039 --> 01:57:04,939
What are you doing?

1262
01:57:09,812 --> 01:57:11,109
Of the proud Mende tribe.

1263
01:57:17,053 --> 01:57:21,922
You are a good boy
who loves soccer and school.

1264
01:57:24,226 --> 01:57:27,354
Your mother loves you so much.

1265
01:57:29,799 --> 01:57:32,597
She waits by the fire making plantains...

1266
01:57:32,768 --> 01:57:35,430
...and red palm oil stew
with your sister N'Yanda...

1267
01:57:37,707 --> 01:57:39,971
...and the new baby.

1268
01:57:48,884 --> 01:57:51,148
The cows wait for you.

1269
01:57:51,320 --> 01:57:57,122
And Babu, the wild dog
who minds no one but you.

1270
01:57:59,695 --> 01:58:03,028
I know they made you do bad things...

1271
01:58:03,199 --> 01:58:05,667
...but you are not a bad boy.

1272
01:58:08,871 --> 01:58:11,271
I am your father...

1273
01:58:12,975 --> 01:58:15,273
...who loves you.

1274
01:58:16,545 --> 01:58:20,311
And you will come home with me
and be my son again.

1275
01:58:45,741 --> 01:58:48,107
Solomon, we've got to move, huh?

1276
01:58:48,277 --> 01:58:49,835
We've got to--

1277
01:58:53,015 --> 01:58:55,711
Go, go! Move!

1278
01:58:58,487 --> 01:59:00,045
Move. Move.

1279
01:59:00,222 --> 01:59:01,519
Move, move, move!

1280
01:59:01,690 --> 01:59:04,716
Move! Move! Move!

1281
01:59:06,328 --> 01:59:07,556
How far?

1282
01:59:07,730 --> 01:59:09,789
There's an airstrip
at the top of that gorge.

1283
01:59:09,965 --> 01:59:12,058
A plane will meet us, huh?

1284
01:59:12,468 --> 01:59:14,834
Hey, stop. Stop.

1285
01:59:17,106 --> 01:59:21,099
Give it to me.
Come on, give it to me, huh?

1286
01:59:28,617 --> 01:59:31,677
Keep moving. They'll be tracking us.

1287
01:59:37,993 --> 01:59:40,052
Nabil, where are you?

1288
01:59:41,130 --> 01:59:43,758
I'm nearly there.
Tell me what's happening.

1289
01:59:43,933 --> 01:59:47,391
We're about 10 K's out, huh?
We've got it, my friend.

1290
01:59:47,570 --> 01:59:49,470
- Who is we?
- The fisherman and his son.

1291
01:59:49,638 --> 01:59:51,230
Lose them.

1292
02:00:05,387 --> 02:00:07,480
It's at the top of that ridge there, huh?

1293
02:00:07,656 --> 02:00:08,953
You must stop and rest.

1294
02:00:09,125 --> 02:00:11,958
What? And give up the damn stone?

1295
02:00:12,128 --> 02:00:14,187
Keep moving. Come on.

1296
02:00:48,831 --> 02:00:51,163
Come. Come, come.

1297
02:01:38,280 --> 02:01:40,578
I can't. Stop.

1298
02:01:40,749 --> 02:01:42,808
- Okay.
- Stop.

1299
02:02:11,280 --> 02:02:12,372
Come on.

1300
02:02:12,982 --> 02:02:15,576
No! God, no. Stop.

1301
02:02:16,685 --> 02:02:20,018
Christ. No more. No more.

1302
02:03:03,966 --> 02:03:05,661
Take it, huh?

1303
02:03:08,070 --> 02:03:11,267
- Mr. Archer--
- Take it, take it.

1304
02:03:18,347 --> 02:03:20,110
I thought you would steal it from me.

1305
02:03:21,950 --> 02:03:25,579
Yeah, yeah, it occurred to me, huh?

1306
02:03:36,532 --> 02:03:38,159
Listen...

1307
02:03:41,136 --> 02:03:43,536
...this is Maddy's card, huh?

1308
02:03:43,706 --> 02:03:45,867
You call her when
you get to Conakry, all right?

1309
02:03:50,112 --> 02:03:52,080
And don't trust that pilot for a second.

1310
02:03:52,247 --> 02:03:55,307
You point this at his head
if he fucks around, all right?

1311
02:03:55,484 --> 02:03:56,951
I can carry you.

1312
02:04:09,865 --> 02:04:11,332
You take your boy home, huh?

1313
02:04:16,505 --> 02:04:19,167
You take him home, huh?

1314
02:04:23,712 --> 02:04:25,475
- Go! Go!
- Go. Come on.

1315
02:04:26,315 --> 02:04:27,407
Go on!

1316
02:04:33,155 --> 02:04:35,020
Come on. Come on.

1317
02:04:41,830 --> 02:04:44,196
Archer, you're a dead man!

1318
02:04:44,366 --> 02:04:46,197
Yeah, yeah.

1319
02:05:16,899 --> 02:05:18,264
Dia.

1320
02:05:39,488 --> 02:05:40,648
Hello. Maddy Bowen.

1321
02:05:40,889 --> 02:05:42,720
Yeah.

1322
02:05:43,058 --> 02:05:44,719
Thought I'd never call, huh?

1323
02:05:45,627 --> 02:05:49,688
And I'm so glad you did.
Excuse me.

1324
02:05:51,667 --> 02:05:52,827
When am I gonna see you?

1325
02:05:53,969 --> 02:05:59,703
Maddy, I want you to do me
one more favor, huh?

1326
02:06:00,409 --> 02:06:04,937
I want you to go meet Solomon
in Conakry.

1327
02:06:05,147 --> 02:06:07,843
In Guinea?
Why do you want me to go to Guinea?

1328
02:06:10,853 --> 02:06:12,912
We found his son...

1329
02:06:13,889 --> 02:06:17,290
...but he's gonna need some help,
you understand?

1330
02:06:18,060 --> 02:06:19,152
Maddy?

1331
02:06:21,964 --> 02:06:23,829
You're hurt.

1332
02:06:24,466 --> 02:06:25,524
Are you hurt?

1333
02:06:25,701 --> 02:06:28,864
Yeah, well, I've got
a little problem here.

1334
02:06:33,442 --> 02:06:37,139
Okay. You--
You tell me where you are.

1335
02:06:40,415 --> 02:06:41,439
Archer?

1336
02:06:53,595 --> 02:06:58,328
I'm looking at an incredible view
right now.

1337
02:06:59,735 --> 02:07:01,362
I wish you were here, Maddy.

1338
02:07:01,537 --> 02:07:05,200
Okay, then I'm coming to be with you.
You just tell me where you are.

1339
02:07:08,410 --> 02:07:09,741
I don't think so.

1340
02:07:09,912 --> 02:07:13,245
Are you still in Kono? Because I can
get someone there to help you.

1341
02:07:13,415 --> 02:07:17,681
Maddy, you find someplace safe
for the boy, all right?

1342
02:07:17,853 --> 02:07:20,253
And keep him out of sight.

1343
02:07:20,856 --> 02:07:23,586
And get Solomon to London.

1344
02:07:26,728 --> 02:07:29,492
He's bringing something with him.

1345
02:07:30,165 --> 02:07:32,099
But he's gonna need your help.

1346
02:07:33,335 --> 02:07:35,166
Why aren't you bringing it yourself?

1347
02:07:36,672 --> 02:07:41,735
I'm saying it's a real story now.

1348
02:07:42,644 --> 02:07:44,373
And you can write the hell out of it.

1349
02:07:51,587 --> 02:07:54,112
I'm really happy I met you.

1350
02:07:55,691 --> 02:07:56,680
You know that?

1351
02:08:00,028 --> 02:08:02,155
Yeah, I'm...

1352
02:08:03,365 --> 02:08:06,425
I'm really happy I met you too.

1353
02:08:07,035 --> 02:08:11,028
And I wish I could be there with you.

1354
02:08:11,907 --> 02:08:13,875
That's all right.

1355
02:08:16,411 --> 02:08:18,811
I'm exactly where I'm supposed to be.

1356
02:09:12,434 --> 02:09:14,766
When we get to the stairs,
you just keep walking...

1357
02:09:14,936 --> 02:09:16,961
...and I'll wait for you here.

1358
02:09:17,539 --> 02:09:19,063
You're not coming.

1359
02:09:19,241 --> 02:09:22,506
I'm not here. Good luck.

1360
02:09:44,166 --> 02:09:46,828
You must understand, Mr. Vandy...

1361
02:09:47,002 --> 02:09:53,066
...that your diamond could have ended up
nowhere else but with us.

1362
02:09:56,380 --> 02:09:59,345
- It is not enough.
- I assure you, 2 million pounds...

1363
02:09:59,515 --> 02:10:03,380
...is more than anyone else will offer you
for that stone under the circumstances.

1364
02:10:03,550 --> 02:10:06,250
I want what was promised to me
by Mr. Archer.

1365
02:10:09,725 --> 02:10:12,250
- What was promised to you?
- My family.

1366
02:10:12,595 --> 02:10:14,585
When they are here,
you will get the stone.

1367
02:10:15,265 --> 02:10:16,890
I will have the money too.

1368
02:10:18,200 --> 02:10:19,725
Well, may I see what I'm buying?

1369
02:10:19,900 --> 02:10:22,665
You will get the stone
once my family is here.

1370
02:10:23,440 --> 02:10:25,235
How do I even know you've got it?

1371
02:12:33,135 --> 02:12:35,900
Can you comment on the diamonds
mined in Sierra Leone?

1372
02:12:36,070 --> 02:12:39,975
I'm not going to comment
on some sensationalist magazine article.

1373
02:12:40,140 --> 02:12:42,735
- What about Liberia?
- No comment. No comment.

1374
02:12:42,910 --> 02:12:45,310
- Mr. Van De Kaap--
- That's all I have to say.

1375
02:12:45,480 --> 02:12:46,880
The natural resources
of a country...

1376
02:12:48,885 --> 02:12:51,855
...are the property of its people.
They are not ours to steal...

1377
02:12:53,190 --> 02:12:58,650
...or exploit in the name of our comfort,
our corporations, or our consumerism.

1378
02:13:08,570 --> 02:13:10,630
They're ready for you, sir.

1379
02:13:12,140 --> 02:13:14,540
The Third World is not a world apart.

1380
02:13:14,710 --> 02:13:19,375
And the witness you will hear today
speaks on its behalf.

1381
02:13:19,545 --> 02:13:23,415
Let us hear the voice of that world.
Let us learn from that voice.

1382
02:13:23,585 --> 02:13:27,110
And let us ignore it no more.

1383
02:13:27,290 --> 02:13:30,620
Ladies and gentlemen,
Mr. Solomon Vandy.

